        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-01-31T20:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-01-31T20:00:00-05:00" n="1235" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1235">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">125.0093/1–3049: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in the Philippines</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Lockett</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-01-31T20:00:00-05:00">January 31, 1949—8 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>116. Re Nanking’s 275, Jan 30 to Dept, rptd Manila 15. No action should be taken
                    re return evacuated dependents to China pending receipt Dept’s further
                    instructions.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
